title: For Trade:  S&W M&P40c
postcontent:
I have an almost new S&W M&P40c that I'm thinking of trading for something different.  I bought it new just last month (have receipt to prove it) and have put exactly 251 rounds through it.  Absolutely nothing wrong with it and it has functioned flawlessly for me, but after having a few striker fire guns I just can't get over the fact that I prefer SA or SA/DA over striker fired ones.

So, I'm interested in trading for something along these lines in .40 caliber.

I'm most interested in a SIG p239 (in .40), I've handled a few and like the way they feel in my hand and I like the thinness of the single stack design.

This is what I'm most interested in, but I may also consider a Beretta PX4 Storm Subcompact (NOT the compact) and other .40 cal options with an exposed hammer, SA or SA/DA in a subcompact or compact size.  

Would also be interested in an American made 1911, nothing against Rock Islands and the like but I want something of a bit higher quality if I'm going to be carrying it.  I would prefer a commander size but may still consider a full sized 1911. 

My M&P includes the box, lock, paperwork, backstraps, 3 magazines (one with the extended pinky grip, two with flat baseplates), and two holsters, one IWB, the other OWB.  I'd love a trade for the same number of mags, as most of us know they can be pricey and hard to come by.

FTF only in wichita, only interested in trades so please do not ask for a sale price.  I do not need to get rid of this, just seeing what else is out there.  This is my carry gun so I will want to include a bill of sale to protect both of us.
Send offers and pictures of what you have through email and I will get back to you if I'm interested, thanks!

title: For Trade:  Gunners...Please Use your FLAG Option
postcontent:
Real Gunners Please... ONE Flag CAN make a Difference! And it takes less than 3 seconds to make a stand and say, "No More!"

"No More"  $.50- $1.00 a round
"No More"  USED firearms at or above a NEW firearm's price
"No More"  Craigslist Items  

There is an "Over-Priced" radio button in the "FLAG" section... right over the "Contact Seller" option. Guys... lets get together and use the tools provided to us to stop all these rookies trying to sell a USED!! firearm for more than what it can be bought for NEW in a store! Or Ammunition at TRIPLE! the cost.

Use the "Spam" option for the Craigslist Items and ArmsList will keep them from posting anything else...

Armslist used to be a great place where good people got together and shared their passions for firearms... now it's a price-gouging, yard-sale (almost the new Craigslist) that makes absolutely no sense...

**EXAMPLE**:   a USED Glock for $800???? That's a $300-$350 firearm- no matter what model and condition. There is nothing special about it... it's not a collectible (unless it's an 18 and good luck getting your hands on one of those); they made them by the hundreds of thousands- EVERY YEAR. Not to mention- THEY ARE TRYING TO BAN ASSAULT RIFLES... NOT PISTOLS???  Again... Get real!!

ArmsList has a threshold (certain number of "flags") that has to be reached before it will be removed, so please don't just sit there and b*tch about these guys- Do Something About Them and FLAG them OFF of here until they come to their senses and stop trying to take advantage of their fellow Gun Owner, Neighbor, Possibly a Soldier, and American Citizen. 

So like I wrote earlier... ONE Flag CAN make a Difference cause yours might be the one that crosses that threshold.. 

Stay Vigilant.. Hold the Line... and FIRE (flag) when you see a Predator's ad up.

We have the Technology... Use it.

Semper Fi

"Custom" = put together with gun show junk parts

"Loaded" = every piece of NC Star gear that can possibly fit on any weapon

"Rare"    = there are about 10-15 of them at Gander Mt.

"NIB"     = been finger fucked every day for the last few months

"Tactical Shotgun" = Normal Shotgun with a Pistol Grip

"Never Been Fired" = bought for the sole purpose of being resold for more money

"Hard to Find Ammo" = it's Hard to Find because Assholes like the sellers are buying it all up only to sell it for a profit

"I have plenty of Ammo" = I have no job or life, so I sit outside Gander Mt. everyday and buy it all before you can

"Last Box of 22lr Ammo" = I have 50 more boxes I got from Wal-Mart , Gander, and Dick's, and will post a new add tomorrow

"Price Firm" = I am delusional, and want bags of money for my Used gun

"Made in Italy" = I am hoping you know nothing about guns and will think I am selling you something special

"Get it Before the Gub'mint Takes Them" = kooks that bury ammo in their yard and horde cans of soup and batteries

"Please Don't Waste My Time" = I am a douche bag, and have already been told by the Arms List Community many times before.

"Willing to Trade, Let Me Know" = I will only trade my stock Ruger 10/22 for a Solid Gold Anti-Tank cannon and $10,000 from you. 

"Please no Black Powders or Non Gun Items" = Open to Pit Bull Puppies, Flea Market Gold Chains, and Guitar Amps 

I have worked at gun stores in Alaska, Texas, and Colorado. This site makes me smile on a daily basis. Have a good one guys.

title: Want To Buy:  Want to Trade for a Tactical .22lr or Shotgun
location: stl, potosi, sullivan, St. Louis, Missouri
postcontent:
i have a 14.5' trailer frame that i planned on building a portable mini-cabin on for hunting and camping. about a week after i got it down to the frame, i found a 32 ft. camper for next to nothing and had to jump on the deal. needless to say, i don't need to build a portable cabin anymore.

the frame is straight, has 2 descent tires that hold air and a spare that's flat, brakes work once they're wired back onto the harness, and the lights worked before i took them off, so the harness is fully functional. all you'd need to do is add some decking and a $20 light kit from autozone and you could have a nice little toy hauler or flatbed trailer. or you could do what i was going to do and build a mini-cabin, duck-blind, etc. on it and have something that's portable and handy for the outdoors.

i also have a very nice ibanez acoustic/electric guitar that i bought less than a month ago for $500. i've only picked it up once....i have other guitars that are my main players and i haven't done anything but tune it and strum a couple songs to see how it sounded. bought it as a backup, but i'm no longer going to play anywhere but family functions, so i don't have to have a backup guitar now.

also have an epiphone acoustic guitar that's worth around $200. it's been played, but there's no major wear and tear on it at all.

WILL TRADE FOR:

i'm looking for a .22lr tactical rifle with collapsible stock, scope, 30+ rd mags, etc. to teach my girlfriend to shoot on. needs to have a collapsible stock so it can be adjusted for me and her both....i'm much taller and have a much longer reach than her. needs to be a .22lr because ammo is cheap and it's probably going to take a lot of it to get her to hit the target. also, anything bigger than that would probably kick too hard for her. she can't handle my british 303 long branch rifle, and that's the only thing i currently use.

may also trade for the right home defense shotgun...that way i don't have to teach her to shoot, she can just point it at an intruder and pull the trigger and it'll pepper the heck out of them.

lemme know what you have and which of my items you'd be interested in trading it for. thanks.

please don't flag this ad and put it in miscellaneous again.  i'm posting it in the firearms section because that's what i'm looking to trade for.  i'm not looking for someone that's searching to BUY a trailer frame or guitars or i'd just list it in miscellaneous with a price.  looking to trade, not sell.  so please leave my ad where it is, folks.  i'm not being rude or mean or a jerk about it, just would like it to stay where the people that i'm looking to trade with will see it.  thanks.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Like New 1931 Colt Detective Special w/German Import Marks and a "Colt Letter"
postcontent:
I am looking to sell this revolver or trade it for a Colt Python in like condition.  This is a rare 1931 Colt Detective Special and not a Police Positive turned into a Detective Special.  It was delivered originally to the Peters Arms Company. This was a division of the Peters Cartridge Company with is today the "P" portion of Remington ammo when you see the "R-P" stamped into the shell casings.  Colt sold this pistol to Peters Arms on September 9, 1931.  Sometime between this date and 1939 it was imported into Germany.  This is a big deal because Hitler was in control by then and no civilian could own a firearm at that time.  I know it was not imported later than that because the proof stamps used by this armory were not used after 1939 when Germany went to war with the world.  You can do the research yourself if you like and the proof stamps are very clear as a crown over a crown and a "U" laying on its side (a.k.a. Cc/U or C/C/U proof marks).  This website will give more information if you wish to confirm for yourself: http://www.germanguns.com/gun-marks . This Pistol also has a "T" stamped over the serial number which indicated this revolver was not just test fired at the factory but was actually "Targeted" by the factory.  This pistol does not appear to have been fired after the factory.  It was also custom fit for someone because the "square butt" grips were modified to the 1933 style "round butt".  Whom ever did the modifications was a pure craftsman because it looks like it was done by the factory.

Anyway, I could go on-and-on about the history and uniqueness of this revolver.  I will answer any questions as best I can.  This is a serious bit of Colt and Possibly W.W.II history.  I am asking $1850 for this pistol or will trade it for a Colt Python in like condition.  Please email me with your name and contact information.  I will not respond to low-ball offers, rude people or ridiculous trade offers.  I prefer a Face-to-Face trade but if you are out of Albuquerque and have a Python I will discuss trade options with you but it may not be easy to do for either of us...  But we can talk about it.

(Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding.
